      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0636P0-00875'>
        <a name='S5LV0636P0_20020611_GCR_88'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-thomas-dixon' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0636P0_20020611_GCR_88' title='Link to this speech by Mr Thomas Dixon' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-thomas-dixon" title="Mr Thomas Dixon">Lord Glentoran</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            moved Amendment No. 14:
            <q>Page 2, line 39, at end insert&#x2014;</q>
            <q>() Any person who has, at any time, been sentenced to a term of imprisonment whether suspended or otherwise for a term in excess of six months shall not be permitted to be appointed as a member under subsection (5).</q>
            The noble Lord said: I have already spoken briefly to Amendment No. 14. I beg to move.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
