          <p class='first-para'>
            I thought the noble Baroness understood that we understand that the Government want flexibility, but a number of us do not wish the
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_31gc' title='Col. 31GC &mdash; HL Deb 11 June 2002 vol 636 c31GC' name='column_31gc' href='#column_31gc' rel='bookmark'>31GC</a>
            Government to have that flexibility, and for very good reason. It is no good the noble Baroness talking about people who in their youth have committed some minor offence&#x2014;I do not know what she has in mind; perhaps shoplifting in Woolworth's&#x2014;and then gone on to lead a blameless life. We are not talking about people who were shoplifting in Woolworth's; we are talking about people who were murdering, bombing and wounding.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
